review_blob: Poured from a 22. Color is light and it looks very refreshing. Flavor is crisp and mild. It actually does taste refreshing and light! The flavor has some sweet fruit hints and finishes crisp. Great beer!
Poured from a 22. Aroma is nutty, grassy and caramel. Flavor has a nice hop punch at first, balanced out by sweet grass syrupy and nutty. Interesting beer, drinks "thick" and is packed with flavor.
beer_name: Laurelwood Green Mammoth Organic Imperial IPA

review_blob: Had on tap at ParkStone near the PDX Airport. Aroma is roasty. Flavor is chalky and a bit sweet. Very easy drinking beer, finishes slightly bitter and astringent.

Had on tap at the brew pub in McMinnville, OR. Aroma is strong coffee. Flavor has a strong coffee, roasty, and sweet flavor to it. Overall a very smooth beer, not bitter at all. One of the better coffee stouts I have had!
Poured from a 22. Has a sweet and floral start. Flavors of caramel, wood and resin. Finishes slightly sharp and astringent.
Poured from a 12. Aroma is slightly pencil shaving-like. Flavor is bitter, dank and slightly creamy. Definitely more of a grassy, earthy IPA.
Poured from a 12. Aroma has a slight caramel nose. First flavor is sweet, crisp and very carbonated. Finishes dank, like a Bud, and really bitter.
Poured from a 22. Aroma is a bit grassy but not overwhelming. Flavor is slightly bitter to start and then evens out to a light hay/grassy and then sweet like melon. Clean, easy beer drinking beer!
Had on tap at Laughing Planet in Portland. Aroma is slightly hoppy. Flavor is a bit tart at first. The flavor then becomes lemony and smooth. Great easy drinking beer!
Poured from a 22. Aroma is sweet, caramel like. Flavor has a sharp, not yet ripe apple taste to it. Really makes my mouth pucker. Finishes very bitter and astringent.

Poured from a growler filled at Portland Fruit West in Beaverton. Pours dark and inviting. Aroma is clean and hoppy. Flavor is crisp at first then grassy and slightly roasty, finishes bitter and astringent. Very easy drinking beer.

Had on tap at the Country Cruise In Diner in Hillsboro, OR. Aroma is floral, hoppy. Flavor is sweet, floral and tropical fruit like. Has a bit of a pencil shaving bite to the finish, but overall pretty great.
Had on tap at the Country Cruise In Diner in Hillsboro, OR. Aroma is licorice and slightly roasty. Flavor has a bit of licorice and vanilla. Is a bit watery in the mouth feel but pretty smooth.
Poured from a bottle. Aroma is floral and skunky. Taste is definitely Belgian but also hoppy. Has a bit of sourness at first and then floral and skunky. Not bad, but interesting blend of flavors.
Had on tap at the Brewery. Aroma is floral and hoppy. Flavor is sweet, grapefruity, and slightly creamy and bitter. Decent IPA.
Had on tap at the Brewery. Aroma is strangely grapey. Flavor is bitter and burnt. Finishes extremely bitter and astringent.
Had on tap at the Brewery. Not much to the aroma. Flavor is thin and watery. Has a little bit of roasty flavor at the end.
Poured from a 22. Aroma is roasty and malty. Flavor is bitter, roasty and slightly burnt.

Poured from a 12. Aroma is not overly strong on cherry but there is a fruit aroma there. Flavor is light, slightly tart (not as tart as I was expecting), cherry and lemon. Has a bit of a bite in the finish. Not as terrible as I was expecting based on the name/style.
beer_name: No-Li Mosh Pit Tart Cherry Ale

review_blob: Poured from a 22. Best coffee stout out there. Aroma is just like a coffee shop, strong and sweet. Flavor is definitely coffee and not bitter at all. Has a slight chocolatey creaminess to it. Nice smooth finish and the coffee flavor really stays with you. Perfect!
beer_name: Laurelwood Organic Portland Roast Espresso Stout

review_blob: Poured from a 22. Aroma is hoppy and floral. Flavor is smooth, slightly biscuit and citrus. Nothing too overpowering here. Finish has a bit of a bite to it. Overall easy drinking beer!

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Poured from a 12. Aroma is boozy and fruity - raspberry and cherry. Flavor is biscuit with chocolate and caramel at first. The boozy, fruity flavor is at the end of the taste. Finishes somewhat sharp and astringent.
beer_name: Leinenkugels Big Eddy Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Poured from a 22. Aroma is caramel cotton candy sweet. Flavor is very sweet and has a bitter bite to it. The beer is a little too sweet for me, but overall not bad.
Poured at the brewery in McMinnville, OR. Aroma is hoppy, malty and sweet. Flavor is grassy, malty, and peppery. Has a bit of caramel and bread. Smooth finish. Easy drinking beer!
beer_name: Grain Station Bet the Farm IPA

review_blob: Poured from a 12. Aroma is roasty, sweet and milky. Flavor is chocolatey, bitter, creamy and boozy. The finish is slightly tart but overall a great beer.
beer_name: Evil Twin Christmas Eve at a New York City Hotel Room (2011-)

review_blob: Poured from a 22. Aroma is hoppy. Flavor is cherry, medicinal and piney. Burns a bit going down. Im sure this is a standard Barleywine, but this is not my favorite style.
beer_name: No-Li Expo Series Big Bang Barley Wine

review_blob: Poured from a growler purchased at Portland Fruit West. Aroma is pot and skunk. Flavor has the initial dankness to it mixed with pencil shavings. There is some bitterness there but I didnt get any citrus. It does grow on you and turns into an easy drinking beer.
Poured from a 12 oz bottle. Aroma is hoppy and grassy. Flavor is grassy, grapefruity and slightly sour. Has a nice long bitter finish.

Poured from a can. You can really smell the fresh hop in the aroma. Flavor has a bit of the Belgian skunk to it at first, but it is very light. Has some barnyard, clove, and grass to it. Finish is crisp and clean.
Poured from a 12 oz can. Aroma is chalky and somewhat chocolatey. Flavor is surprisingly boozy at first, cherry and a bit fake chocolate-like. Feels a bit watery and chalky in the finish.
Poured from a bottle. Aroma is barnyard, sweet and grassy. Flavor is sweet, grassy and bitter with a sharp hoppy flavor. As the beer warms it has a slight caramel flavor to it.

Poured from a 12. Aroma is slightly coffee. The flavor yields most of the coffee characteristics. It is coffee at first and sweet to finish. Has a slight bitterness at first with the coffee flavor finishes creamy.

Poured from a 22. Aroma is like an overspiced winter ale. Flavor is sweet like cotton candy at first and then a bit skunky to finish. Couldnt quite place all the flavors, mostly fake orange and cotton candy. Has a creamy mouth feel, like a bad cream soda.
beer_name: Alameda Bad Bunny Imperial Cream Ale

review_blob: Poured from a 500ml bottle. Looks like a Belgian. Aroma is sweet grass. Flavor is slightly tart, grassy and creamy. Has a very light mouth feel with a slightly bitter and citrusy finish.
Poured from a 22. Aroma is citrusy and hoppy. Flavor is citrus fruit, creamy and hoppy. Finish is bitter and slightly astringent.
Poured from a 22. Aroma is hoppy and citrus. Flavor is a little citrusy sour at first and then a bit sweet like tropical fruit. Finishes creamy.
Poured from a 22. Aroma is citrusy, sour, and a bit skunky. Flavor is ChapStick and Pinesol. As the beer warms it grows on you...but still not great. Tastes more skunky than fruity.

Poured from a bottle on an Alaska Air flight to Boise. Aroma is somewhat floral. Flavor is garden like, salty and creamy. Doesnt have that normal harsh bitter bite of a red. Instead tastes more like a BBQ. Interesting beer!

Drank from a 12 oz bottle. Aroma is your standard beer aroma. Flavor is slightly bitter at first and then yields to a slight sweet and crisp beer. Does have any strong seasonal spices to it, which I like! Nice, easy drinking seasonal!
Had on tap at the brewery. Aroma is sweet, caramel and roasty. Flavor is sweet, smore like, roasty and creamy. Great beer. Enough said.
beer_name: Woodland Empire Cozy Up Big Ol Milk Stout

review_blob: Had on tap at the brewery. Aroma is slightly woody and smokey. Flavor is sweet, woody, slightly smokey. Has a creamy taste and clean, crisp, smooth finish. Great beer!

Had on tap at the brewery. Aroma is rich, thick, malty, roasty with chocolate hints. Flavor is creamy at first, roasty, and slightly bitter. Flavor has slight hints of chocolate and sweetness. Great beer, not at all boozy for an imperial.
beer_name: Slanted Rock After Midnight Imperial Stout

review_blob: Had on tap at the brewery. Aroma has hints of vanilla. Flavor is a bit chalky, but sweet. Definitely has a vanilla taste. After taste is a bit metallic but overall not bad.
Poured from a 12. Has a nice strong ale aroma. Flavor is slightly bitter, caramel and creamy. Doesnt have all the crazy, overspiced flavor to it, which is awesome! Great seasonal beer!
Poured from a 12. Aroma is dank and barnyard. Flavor is sharp, bitter and a bit sour like grapefruit. Not very complex.
beer_name: Green Flash Hop Odyssey Mosaic Session IPA

review_blob: Poured from a 12. Aroma is malty, roasty and dry. Flavor is malty, dry and a bit bitter. Pretty drinkable for a porter.
Poured from a 12. Aroma is very piney and grassy. Flavor is very hoppy and grassy. Finish is a great bitter hoppy finish with a slightly sweet flavor left over.

Poured from a 12. Aroma is berry, spruce and Christmas. Flavor is berry sweet, but like artificial berry flavor. Has a lip balm flavor to it. Finish is fairly smooth, but the sweetness does not sit well in my stomach.

Poured from a 12. Appearance is very light and cloudy. Aroma is definitely fresh cucumber, like how your kitchen would smell if you were getting ready to make pickles. Flavor is cucumber (obviously), creamy, pickled garlic and sweet. Yeah, I know that sounds gross, but it is surprisingly light and refreshing.

Poured from a 12. Aroma is a bit dry and chalky. Flavor has a bitter/astringent bite at first. After the beer warms it smooths out a bit and has a dark chocolate and grainy flavor to it. Finishes a bit creamy.
